13/11/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Council of Europe (CoE) Secretary General Terry Davis met with Macedonian Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva and Minister of Local Self-Government Rizvan Sulejmani on Saturday (12 November) and welcomed Macedonia's progress in the decentralisation process.
He also expressed satisfaction with the co-operation of Macedonian and Albanian local governments and the strengthening of regional co-operation within the context of Macedonia's EU accession process.
Mitreva, meanwhile, said CoE membership was helping her country strengthen democracy and boost respect for human rights.
(MIA, A1 TV - 12/11/05)
